1
00:00:07,559 --> 00:00:09,160
You can't post this photo on Weibo.

2
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:10,320
Why not?

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,080
Aren't you afraid of scaring your fans?

4
00:00:12,320 --> 00:00:13,480
I'll just blur it out.

5
00:00:17,519 --> 00:00:18,920
You don't post on Weibo often.

6
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:20,320
What's up with you lately?

7
00:00:21,079 --> 00:00:22,519
Just in a good mood all of a sudden.

8
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:34,500
"A Winter Sun Wakes the Wind in Spring Hills' Dream"

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,800
(Episode 3: Ji Zongjun)

10
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,759
Want anything else to eat?

11
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:49,920
This is enough.

12
00:00:50,003 --> 00:00:51,883
[A fan is asking why he
blurred the first photo]

13
00:00:51,910 --> 00:00:54,363
[Ji Zongjun asks who made the meal]

14
00:00:58,679 --> 00:00:59,679
There's a problem.

15
00:01:01,119 --> 00:01:02,560
I made a post on Weibo.

16
00:01:02,679 --> 00:01:03,959
It said, "Unstoppable momentum."

17
00:01:04,359 --> 00:01:05,920
Then Shi Yuhao posted one too.

18
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:07,280
It said, "Clear skies."

19
00:01:08,120 --> 00:01:09,656
The "shi" in "momentum"
sounds like his last name, Shi.

20
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:12,040
So the fans are interpreting
it as us being together again.

21
00:01:12,319 --> 00:01:14,000
That's what fans do, isn't it?

22
00:01:14,519 --> 00:01:15,999
But I don't want to be misunderstood.

23
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:18,919
I don't want what the fans see...

24
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:21,096
to be completely different
from what they're guessing.

25
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:22,480
It's not fair to them.

26
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:25,799
Then do you dare tell them the truth?

27
00:01:26,959 --> 00:01:28,760
It's not that I don't dare to, I can't.

28
00:01:29,599 --> 00:01:30,519
If I told them,

29
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,399
the ones who believe would get hurt.

30
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,495
And the ones who don't
believe would just start fighting.

31
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:36,920
Some truths are just
destined to never be told.

32
00:01:38,519 --> 00:01:39,599
Can you delete it?

33
00:01:43,519 --> 00:01:44,559
I always thought your account...

34
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,800
was managed by your company.

35
00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:49,599
Not entirely. I post myself
when I have free time.

36
00:01:50,159 --> 00:01:52,359
The company handles most
of the business-related posts.

37
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,519
Just eat. Don't post recklessly next time.

38
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,799
Their interpretation has no real evidence.

39
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:03,335
Tell him if he doesn't
want to act, he can get out.

40
00:02:03,359 --> 00:02:04,878
If we change the script to his demands,

41
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:06,159
will the show even be watchable?

42
00:02:08,319 --> 00:02:10,359
The crew over at Lengdian
is causing trouble again.

43
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,360
That actor Qi Haoyu's company swapped in...

44
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,758
keeps trying to change the script.

45
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:16,159
He won't act if we don't change it.

46
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,360
We're not putting up with that.

47
00:02:18,879 --> 00:02:20,959
How many big productions
are even running right now?

48
00:02:21,199 --> 00:02:22,319
If he doesn't want the part,

49
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,800
there's a line of people who do.

50
00:02:24,319 --> 00:02:26,800
He's not a big star, but he's a big pain.

51
00:02:27,879 --> 00:02:29,560
You never should have agreed to the swap.

52
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:33,200
Haven't we learned our lesson from
what we went through with Shi Yuhao?

53
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:36,440
Qi Haoyu's acting is
genuinely good, though.

54
00:02:44,319 --> 00:02:45,120
What are you doing?

55
00:02:45,121 --> 00:02:46,360
You're sending me to Molie...

56
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,640
it's not like it's goodbye forever.

57
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,560
There's something I've
been meaning to tell you.

58
00:02:54,319 --> 00:02:57,479
No outsiders knew that
Qinglang was in Molie.

59
00:02:58,319 --> 00:03:00,079
But Shi Yuhao managed to find him there.

60
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:02,680
That means he has a source who
can get information from our side.

61
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,120
Who do you suspect?

62
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:11,560
Sister Jialin, Sister Lan, I'm
here for tomorrow's call sheet.

63
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,960
Aren't you eating?

64
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:35,879
Mmm, so good.

65
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,080
Someone's analyzing that photo.

66
00:03:40,159 --> 00:03:42,199
They're saying the
blurry figure is Shi Yuhao.

67
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,159
The one you took of me.

68
00:03:46,759 --> 00:03:47,879
This is infuriating.

69
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,800
Dare to post it?

70
00:03:57,879 --> 00:03:58,879
I don't dare.

71
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:22,959
Xiao Tanzi.

72
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,120
Are my lips swollen?

73
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,600
Your lips have always been pretty full.

74
00:04:39,879 --> 00:04:40,879
Ugh, it's itchy.

75
00:04:41,319 --> 00:04:42,720
Did I get bitten by a bug?

76
00:04:45,339 --> 00:04:46,498
You're allergic to protein.

77
00:04:46,666 --> 00:04:48,065
But it never happened before.

78
00:04:48,733 --> 00:04:50,293
You just never ate enough of it before.

79
00:05:01,279 --> 00:05:02,519
Couldn't find any cotton swabs.

80
00:05:16,879 --> 00:05:17,879
Ow, my neck.

81
00:05:31,879 --> 00:05:33,279
How long will this take to go down?

82
00:05:34,199 --> 00:05:36,480
It'll go down once the
bugs are out of your system.

83
00:05:37,199 --> 00:05:38,720
But I have a livestream to do.

84
00:05:44,279 --> 00:05:47,518
How about I get you a muzzle?

85
00:05:47,519 --> 00:05:48,959
I'll get you a muzzle.

86
00:06:36,959 --> 00:06:39,000
Let me see.

87
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,999
Only your eyes look normal.

88
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,560
Everywhere else is all swollen.

89
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,399
The swelling needs air.

90
00:07:14,279 --> 00:07:15,879
You need to cool down. No meat today.

91
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,319
I'm not looking. Just take it off.

92
00:07:30,279 --> 00:07:32,759
Did I go too hard on Shi Yuhao before?

93
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,800
Is this my karma?

94
00:07:36,279 --> 00:07:39,199
Bad karma from my words. I
really shouldn't speak ill of others.

95
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:42,560
You just held back what you
should have said for seven years.

96
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:44,000
The two things aren't related.

97
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,879
Do you believe in Buddhism?

98
00:07:48,879 --> 00:07:50,079
I believe in cause and effect.

99
00:07:50,879 --> 00:07:52,519
That wolf I saved back then...

100
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,720
I don't know if it survived.

101
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:57,959
But later, my cousin's dog got sick.

102
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,919
The vet said there was no hope.

103
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,536
A few days later, it miraculously
got better on its own.

104
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:03,295
It lived for another three
years before it passed.

105
00:08:03,319 --> 00:08:05,879
I've always felt that some
things in nature are connected.

106
00:08:06,279 --> 00:08:07,879
The deeper you go into the forest,

107
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:10,879
the deeper that connection becomes.

108
00:08:11,279 --> 00:08:12,279
Ah.

109
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:15,200
So that's why you never wanted
to go back to the city for school.

110
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,240
You wanted to stay in the mountains.

111
00:08:17,759 --> 00:08:19,160
You can study anywhere.

112
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,079
In the city, you deal with people.

113
00:08:21,279 --> 00:08:22,959
In the mountains, you commune with nature.

114
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:25,600
Which one do you think is purer?

115
00:08:27,279 --> 00:08:28,319
I get it now.

116
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:33,279
This is nature helping me purify my body.

117
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,200
Is there any side of you I haven't seen?

118
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,558
You've never seen me swollen like this.

119
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:37,480
Let me see how bad it is.

120
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,480
No need.

121
00:08:53,879 --> 00:08:55,360
I know how to get the swelling down.

122
00:09:10,279 --> 00:09:12,159
Don't run. The path is
slippery in the morning.

123
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,559
I want to find that little stream.

124
00:09:19,519 --> 00:09:21,120
There's a big log under that stream.

125
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:24,919
Rope.

126
00:09:33,919 --> 00:09:34,919
What are you doing?

127
00:09:35,519 --> 00:09:36,519
Tying it on.

128
00:09:44,279 --> 00:09:45,279
You tie it on too.

129
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,519
I won't tie it. I'll hold it.

130
00:09:49,519 --> 00:09:50,360
Follow me.

131
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:51,399
No way.

132
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,240
It's like you're walking a dog.

133
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:56,279
Fine. Let's go.

134
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:22,600
We're here.

135
00:10:28,799 --> 00:10:30,479
Being tied together has its pros and cons.

136
00:10:30,919 --> 00:10:32,479
If we walk together, there are no cons.

137
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,000
Be careful.

138
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:50,080
Okay.

139
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,560
Can meditation reduce swelling?

140
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:27,519
It can.

141
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,960
Don't fall asleep. It's
cold in the mountains.

142
00:12:42,799 --> 00:12:43,879
You was dreaming.

143
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,279
Just now, in my dream,

144
00:12:56,679 --> 00:12:58,120
you walked very far away.

145
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,720
It was like you were acting in a play.

146
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,519
The swelling's gone.

147
00:13:38,279 --> 00:13:39,559
While I was meditating just now,

148
00:13:40,399 --> 00:13:42,360
I felt like I'd lived through a century.

149
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,480
And at the beginning
and end of that century,

150
00:13:48,919 --> 00:13:50,159
you were there.

151
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:01,720
The stream is on.

152
00:15:02,919 --> 00:15:03,919
Coming!

153
00:15:17,919 --> 00:15:19,919
This is the tree that's
80,000 per kilogram.

154
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,359
A few years ago, when the economy was good,

155
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,720
the tea farmers were very wealthy.

156
00:15:23,279 --> 00:15:25,120
How is that any different
from owning a mine?

157
00:15:25,586 --> 00:15:27,066
Of course it's different. Changyang.

158
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:30,799
Why don't you tell my brother what the difference
is between a tea farmer and a mine owner.

159
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:32,720
Minerals are a non-renewable resource.

160
00:15:32,879 --> 00:15:34,080
Tea trees are renewable.

161
00:15:34,759 --> 00:15:37,279
A mine owner gets rich
by extracting and taking.

162
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:39,255
A tea farmer, however,
needs to constantly cultivate.

163
00:15:39,279 --> 00:15:40,719
Only then can they produce good tea.

164
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:43,615
The wild grass that grows
around the tea trees...

165
00:15:43,639 --> 00:15:44,839
the farmers have to weed it.

166
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:46,039
But they can't remove it all.

167
00:15:46,639 --> 00:15:48,855
They have to maintain the
balance of the natural ecosystem.

168
00:15:48,879 --> 00:15:50,720
That's how the tea trees can grow better.

169
00:15:51,039 --> 00:15:53,416
This is the symbiosis between
the tea trees and the wild grass.

170
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:55,176
If you don't pick the
leaves, the tree won't grow.

171
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:57,080
But if you pick too
many, you'll harm the tree.

172
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,720
The tea trees and the wild grass.

173
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:08,720
I want to go up and see too.

174
00:16:08,799 --> 00:16:09,799
Come on.

175
00:16:17,919 --> 00:16:19,600
What are these racks for?

176
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,038
You stand on them when you're picking tea.

177
00:16:22,039 --> 00:16:23,759
That's how you can reach the higher leaves.

178
00:16:26,559 --> 00:16:28,000
Can we climb any higher?

179
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:30,360
You want to climb?

180
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:39,480
Here, you go ahead.

181
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,840
Hey.

182
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:47,519
Let's go home first.

183
00:16:54,679 --> 00:16:55,679
Such bad luck.

184
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:07,680
Did I offend the mountain spirit?

185
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,760
I threw up as soon as
I got to the mountains.

186
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:12,279
My back cramped up,
and my face got swollen.

187
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:14,119
And now my foot is swollen.

188
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,519
Rebirth comes at a price.

189
00:17:17,079 --> 00:17:19,095
Were you like this when you
first came to the mountains?

190
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,680
Felt like I died seven or eight times.

191
00:17:21,559 --> 00:17:22,616
The mountain spirit is wary of outsiders.

192
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:24,440
It has to accept you
as one of its own first.

193
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,280
Why are you taking a picture of me?

194
00:17:33,079 --> 00:17:34,079
Don't send it to Mom.

195
00:17:34,519 --> 00:17:36,359
I'm sending it to someone
who cares about you.

196
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:37,920
Like who?

197
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:39,440
Brother Wenshu.

198
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,680
Why would you send it to him?

199
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:44,240
He asks me for a picture of you every day.

200
00:17:44,279 --> 00:17:46,078
I've been putting him off for days.

201
00:17:46,079 --> 00:17:47,680
I can't exactly tell him...

202
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:50,440
that you're living with his
little brother every day, can I?

203
00:17:52,359 --> 00:17:53,359
Put them on yourself.

204
00:17:56,359 --> 00:17:57,359
Go ahead and send it.

205
00:18:10,079 --> 00:18:11,279
How did you sprain your ankle?

206
00:18:11,839 --> 00:18:13,439
I jumped down from a tree.

207
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,680
And someone failed to catch me.

208
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:18,680
I'll leave you two to talk.

209
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,960
He's gone. I'm hanging up.

210
00:19:02,079 --> 00:19:03,039
If I stay any longer,

211
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:04,920
I'll be black and blue all over.

212
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:06,720
Before the livestream,

213
00:19:06,721 --> 00:19:08,319
you're staying put at home.

214
00:19:08,759 --> 00:19:10,359
I'll make you the plainest meals.

215
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,720
No more coffee, and cut back on the tea.

216
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:15,359
You might as well just tell me to fast.

217
00:19:23,279 --> 00:19:24,279
What are you doing?

218
00:19:24,319 --> 00:19:25,279
Taking you upstairs.

219
00:19:25,279 --> 00:19:26,279
I have work to do.

220
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:27,679
I'm staying on the first floor.

221
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:29,240
No. Upstairs. Time for bed.

222
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:32,440
When you wake up, your foot will be better.

223
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:04,880
You're not that old,

224
00:20:04,881 --> 00:20:06,680
but you give off such a domestic vibe.

225
00:20:11,279 --> 00:20:12,279
Not anymore.

226
00:20:23,256 --> 00:20:26,456
[He's using a nasty AI manga filter to
take a picture of himself for some reason]

227
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:33,510
[He's posting the photo on
Weibo with some obtuse caption]

228
00:20:33,889 --> 00:20:36,569
[Ji Zongjun instantly replies,
remarking that he's in the mountains]

229
00:21:37,863 --> 00:21:42,123
[Between wind, fire, moon and sky.]

230
00:22:33,696 --> 00:22:37,690
[More obtuse posting
while his fans go crazy]

231
00:22:43,839 --> 00:22:45,553
[Ji Zongjun: Am I your flying bird?]

232
00:22:59,906 --> 00:23:00,906
Your foot's all better.

233
00:23:01,359 --> 00:23:02,079
You...

234
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:03,920
Hungry? What do you want to eat?

235
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,480
I want termite mushrooms.

236
00:23:08,839 --> 00:23:09,839
We don't have any today.

237
00:23:25,673 --> 00:23:29,379
[Now he's manic posting about how
he wants to eat termite mushrooms]

238
00:23:36,359 --> 00:23:38,619
[Ji Zongjun: They come out when it rains]

239
00:23:39,913 --> 00:23:42,233
[He's asking this random
poster when it's going to rain???]

240
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:46,839
Damn, what is Lang Di doing? This is bad.

241
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:49,640
Shi Ji Zong.

242
00:23:50,279 --> 00:23:51,559
What is this hashtag?

243
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:05,078
I came up with a ship name.

244
00:24:05,079 --> 00:24:06,480
And I even drew a fan logo.

245
00:24:08,119 --> 00:24:09,240
YuLu Haohan.

246
00:24:09,359 --> 00:24:10,359
A boundless future.

247
00:24:10,839 --> 00:24:11,839
Brilliant, right?

248
00:24:12,279 --> 00:24:13,359
Explain the logo.

249
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:16,840
You think we're definitely
going to get famous?

250
00:24:18,359 --> 00:24:19,359
If not for fame,

251
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:20,640
who would film this?

252
00:24:23,559 --> 00:24:24,999
So what happens after we get famous?

253
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:27,279
After we get famous...

254
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:28,936
Sigh... let's worry about
that when it happens.

255
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:29,960
Explain it.

256
00:24:32,759 --> 00:24:33,759
Sister Lan.

257
00:24:34,359 --> 00:24:36,680
Lang Di gets into trouble
whenever I'm not around.

258
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:39,640
What is it now?

259
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:55,359
My Weibo post just handed
someone else a victory.

260
00:24:56,079 --> 00:24:57,240
I saw.

261
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:58,839
What's with the sudden outburst?

262
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:00,440
Was it an outburst?

263
00:25:00,839 --> 00:25:02,079
I've never seen you like this.

264
00:25:02,359 --> 00:25:04,799
You're someone who can go
half a month without a single post.

265
00:25:05,079 --> 00:25:08,119
Forget it. I just wanted
to vent. I'm hanging up.

266
00:25:08,279 --> 00:25:10,839
Hey, can you show your
investor some respect?

267
00:25:11,839 --> 00:25:14,440
I'll respect you when we
start shooting the next movie.

268
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:20,440
Come in.

269
00:25:24,559 --> 00:25:26,079
There really are no termite mushrooms.

270
00:25:27,079 --> 00:25:28,119
When is it going to rain?

271
00:25:29,039 --> 00:25:30,039
How should I know?

272
00:25:31,839 --> 00:25:33,079
Just make whatever you want.

273
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:34,440
Mm.

274
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,558
Someone posted all of Ji Zongjun's comments

275
00:25:45,559 --> 00:25:47,440
to Lang Di from the past two years.

276
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:51,880
The earliest one was when Lang
Di won an award two years ago.

277
00:25:52,319 --> 00:25:54,039
It was under his acceptance speech.

278
00:25:55,279 --> 00:25:56,279
Watching you.

279
00:25:57,279 --> 00:25:59,599
That really does sound like
something Shi Yuhao would say.

280
00:26:00,039 --> 00:26:02,640
Most fans would just say
something like, "I look up to you."

281
00:26:03,079 --> 00:26:05,079
Shi Yuhao and Qinglang debuted together.

282
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:08,640
Only he would use a
phrase like "watching you."

283
00:26:09,319 --> 00:26:12,039
Sister Lan, what this fan
is saying makes sense.

284
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:14,120
You believe everything the fans say?

285
00:26:14,759 --> 00:26:16,519
Termite mushrooms
are a specialty of Tianyi.

286
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:18,680
What does that have to do with Shi Yuhao?

287
00:26:19,359 --> 00:26:21,479
If you're telling me this Ji Zongjun

288
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:23,439
only started following Qinglang
in the last couple of days,

289
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:25,079
then I might believe he's Shi Yuhao.

290
00:26:26,519 --> 00:26:27,559
That's true.

291
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:30,279
Replying so openly like this,

292
00:26:31,640 --> 00:26:33,119
Lang Di must know who he is.

293
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:35,440
No, I have to call Lang Di.

294
00:26:38,119 --> 00:26:39,119
Oh my god.

295
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:42,039
He posted again. This is killing me.

296
00:26:42,839 --> 00:26:44,519
Is Lang Di about to make things official?

297
00:26:52,863 --> 00:26:54,503
[Another manic post and caption on Weibo]

298
00:26:55,210 --> 00:26:57,330
[Ji Zongjun matches his
mania with a similar response]

299
00:26:57,483 --> 00:27:01,069
[Now they're going back and
forth with their silly little quotes]

300
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:03,839
Jiaozi, Jiaozi!

301
00:27:03,840 --> 00:27:06,559
Help me find out what
book this quote is from.

302
00:27:07,119 --> 00:27:09,078
When the termite mushroom
breaks through the soil,

303
00:27:09,079 --> 00:27:11,759
the treasures of the mountains
can rival any delicacy from the sea.

304
00:27:13,839 --> 00:27:15,758
This quote is from a novel
by the author Shenlai Zhibi.

305
00:27:15,759 --> 00:27:17,839
A Winter Sun Wakes the
Wind in Spring Hills' Dream.

306
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:19,078
The first half of the sentence is,

307
00:27:19,079 --> 00:27:20,359
My distant tea mountains

308
00:27:20,559 --> 00:27:22,439
gaze upon his sea from
thousands of miles away.

309
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:24,359
Sister Lan, look.

310
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,879
Lang Di just posted about this book,

311
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,680
and it's already sold out.

312
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:36,119
Come downstairs. Dinner's ready.

313
00:27:36,319 --> 00:27:38,239
Ah, so Qinglang is the sea,

314
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:39,160
and Shi Yuhao is the mountain.

315
00:27:39,161 --> 00:27:40,838
What a divine metaphor!

316
00:27:40,839 --> 00:27:41,720
Stop forcing the connection.

317
00:27:41,721 --> 00:27:43,078
They said it in the
behind-the-scenes footage.

318
00:27:43,079 --> 00:27:44,319
They both like mountains.

319
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:46,358
What does this Weibo post
have to do with Shi Yuhao?

320
00:27:46,359 --> 00:27:48,279
My 7-year ship has just gone official!

321
00:27:48,519 --> 00:27:51,359
Is this a miracle? Did the
sun just rise in the west?

322
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,720
It can't be Shi Yuhao.

323
00:27:52,839 --> 00:27:53,959
Shi Yuhao is uncultured.

324
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:54,880
He never reads.

325
00:27:54,881 --> 00:27:56,879
How would he possibly know
about such an obscure book?

326
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,319
Who are you calling uncultured?

327
00:28:00,079 --> 00:28:01,959
Didn't you say there were
no termite mushrooms?

328
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:04,560
I have the termite mushroom
oil I made a couple of days ago.

329
00:28:05,079 --> 00:28:06,558
You've completely spoiled my palate.

330
00:28:06,559 --> 00:28:08,879
I won't be able to stand the
boxed lunches on set anymore.

331
00:28:45,839 --> 00:28:48,039
Are you planning to
post on Weibo all night?

332
00:28:48,079 --> 00:28:49,359
I'll stop after dinner.

333
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:51,359
Who is Ji Zongjun?

334
00:28:55,079 --> 00:28:56,079
Not sure.

335
00:28:57,319 --> 00:28:59,880
The arm in that last
GIF, that's him, right?

336
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:02,160
Maybe?

337
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:04,079
Keep your eyes open.

338
00:29:04,160 --> 00:29:06,119
Don't get fooled. Hanging up.

339
00:29:08,079 --> 00:29:10,679
Sister Lan, why didn't you just ask Lang Di

340
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:12,079
what that "Yi Cao" meant?

341
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,480
What "Yi Cao"?

342
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:15,519
Oh, Sister, the Super Topic is blowing up.

343
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:17,680
Lang Di posted a "1" and the letter "C."

344
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:20,119
You have no idea how
the fans are interpreting it.

345
00:29:20,839 --> 00:29:23,319
The "Yi Cao" shippers are
saying the "1" is Shi Yuhao.

346
00:29:23,519 --> 00:29:25,078
Spreading rumors about what they do in bed.

347
00:29:25,079 --> 00:29:26,720
They're completely clueless. [♪gay sigh♪]

348
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:30,079
Call Qingtian.

349
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:32,400
Hurry up and eat. The
noodles are getting soggy.

350
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:36,640
Did you see the Weibo post I just made?

351
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:40,440
You posted again?

352
00:29:40,890 --> 00:29:42,690
[Ji Zongjun: Congrats
on getting to eat some]

353
00:29:44,279 --> 00:29:45,279
Hello?

354
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:46,480
Hello, Brother Guo?

355
00:29:46,759 --> 00:29:47,839
Oh my god.

356
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,120
Bro, can I ask you something?

357
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:51,278
Are you in the mountains?

358
00:29:51,279 --> 00:29:52,896
Did you find a new assistant for Lang Di?

359
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:54,720
No new assistant. Are you kidding?

360
00:29:55,039 --> 00:29:56,759
No one can shake Brother Guo's position.

361
00:29:57,519 --> 00:29:59,559
Oh, I'm dying of anxiety here.

362
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:01,279
Sister Lan has me stuck on set.

363
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:03,815
Lang Di went into the mountains,
and I have no idea where he's run off to.

364
00:30:03,839 --> 00:30:05,160
He's not even answering me.

365
00:30:07,119 --> 00:30:10,160
Who's been taking care of
Lang Di these past few days?

366
00:30:10,519 --> 00:30:12,680
A friend of mine in Molie. A tea farmer.

367
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:16,119
A tea farmer? Can he
handle it? Isn't he clumsy?

368
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:17,440
Changyang is not clumsy at all.

369
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:18,440
He can do anything.

370
00:30:19,839 --> 00:30:22,079
Okay, I get it. God. Hanging up.

371
00:30:24,119 --> 00:30:26,359
Sister Lan, case closed.

372
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:27,920
Ruyuan Yi Cao.

373
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:29,240
Wish come true.

374
00:30:30,039 --> 00:30:31,319
Let me see that picture again.

375
00:30:33,559 --> 00:30:36,519
Oh, this arm belongs to that tea farmer.

376
00:30:37,119 --> 00:30:38,680
Looks pretty strong.

377
00:30:39,279 --> 00:30:40,720
How far have they gotten?

378
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:45,400
They won't let me into the mountains,

379
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:46,800
so I'll just ship them from here.

380
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:56,080
Go into the mountains with me
tomorrow morning, Ji Zongjun.

381
00:30:57,839 --> 00:30:59,399
You're obsessed with termite mushrooms.

382
00:31:01,319 --> 00:31:02,319
Deeply obsessed.

383
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,720
Who is it?

384
00:31:38,079 --> 00:31:39,079
Are you crazy?

385
00:31:51,839 --> 00:31:53,279
Lu, open the door.

386
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:03,440
What are you doing?

387
00:32:04,839 --> 00:32:06,199
Rehearse tomorrow's scene with me.

388
00:32:06,367 --> 00:32:09,480
[He's posting about termite
mushrooms on Weibo yet again!!!!!!!!]

389
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:21,867
[Ji Zongjun is matching
his freak with his response]

390
00:32:58,440 --> 00:32:59,720
I was so tired last night,

391
00:32:59,839 --> 00:33:01,999
I didn't even notice you
didn't come back to the room.

392
00:33:03,960 --> 00:33:06,160
At this point, you're supposed
to put your leg on mine.

393
00:33:06,759 --> 00:33:08,079
Move over.

394
00:33:18,759 --> 00:33:23,559
Do you ever fall for
someone while filming a show?

395
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:27,880
Even if you can't stand them in real life?

396
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:39,559
Is that a line?

397
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:41,839
It's not a line.

398
00:33:42,279 --> 00:33:43,359
I'm asking you.

399
00:34:06,519 --> 00:34:07,839
There's no kissing in this scene.

400
00:34:09,519 --> 00:34:10,879
Let's ask the director to add one.

401
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:35,280
Lu, come back to bed.

402
00:35:29,559 --> 00:35:31,280
A bear! There's a bear!

403
00:35:32,559 --> 00:35:33,559
Run!

404
00:36:26,719 --> 00:36:28,079
Was that a bear just now?

405
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:29,760
Yes.

406
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,280
Is that considered an early bird?

407
00:37:34,639 --> 00:37:35,679
It has a clear call.

408
00:37:37,559 --> 00:37:39,399
The birds that call at
night are even clearer.

409
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:44,600
What's the difference between
early birds and night birds?

410
00:37:47,239 --> 00:37:48,839
Night birds usually call to find a mate.

411
00:37:49,039 --> 00:37:51,279
During mating season, their
calls are even more intense.

412
00:38:02,639 --> 00:38:03,639
Hey.

413
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:01,280
Is the mushroom soup ready to drink?

414
00:39:01,519 --> 00:39:04,399
If you drink it now, I'll be responsible
for taking you to the hospital.

415
00:39:05,280 --> 00:39:06,639
Will I see little people?

416
00:39:08,159 --> 00:39:09,280
You'll meet your maker.

417
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:11,719
I want to see the little people.

418
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:14,040
I don't have that kind of power.

419
00:39:14,280 --> 00:39:15,440
But I've seen it.

420
00:39:17,519 --> 00:39:18,519
What was it like?

421
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:20,840
Like this.

422
00:39:21,559 --> 00:39:22,960
I kept scooping and scooping.

423
00:39:23,239 --> 00:39:24,880
My cousin said I was doing it all night.

424
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:26,519
What did you see?

425
00:39:27,719 --> 00:39:29,639
I saw a big red carp.

426
00:39:29,719 --> 00:39:31,119
I wanted to scoop it up.

427
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:35,360
It was in a pond that was almost dry.

428
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:36,639
It was dying.

429
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:47,840
Changyang.

430
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:50,440
Do you like men?

431
00:39:53,639 --> 00:39:54,639
Does it matter?

432
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:57,639
Answer me directly.

433
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:15,519
You're very clever.

434
00:40:16,519 --> 00:40:19,119
Dodging questions you don't want
to answer with another question.

435
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,239
Hey, don't run off.

436
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:36,639
I'll ask you again.

437
00:40:37,280 --> 00:40:38,559
Do you like men?

438
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:40,960
Is it that important?

439
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:43,480
Fine.

440
00:40:43,920 --> 00:40:45,679
From now on, I won't answer your questions.

441
00:40:45,719 --> 00:40:47,280
And you don't have to answer mine.

442
00:40:47,480 --> 00:40:49,039
We'll just stick to statements.

443
00:40:55,719 --> 00:40:56,919
I'm not trying to brush you off.

444
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:59,200
I can't make promises about
things I haven't figured out.

445
00:41:01,840 --> 00:41:03,639
Do you need to "figure
out" if you like men?

446
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,519
Did I ask you for a promise?

447
00:41:05,679 --> 00:41:07,519
I just asked you a simple question.

448
00:41:09,039 --> 00:41:10,256
You don't dare answer the question.

449
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:12,480
But you're brave enough to
sneak around behind my back.

450
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:15,279
Who was it that set their
computer password to...

451
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:16,640
my birthday and won't admit it?

452
00:41:17,159 --> 00:41:19,639
Whose browser history is full of my movies?

453
00:41:20,639 --> 00:41:23,319
Xu Changyang, you've got the nerve
to want it, but not the guts to admit it.

454
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:25,080
You're cut from the
same cloth as Shi Yuhao.

455
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:30,280
Don't play games with me.

456
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:33,039
The only way you get
out of this is if I let you.

457
00:42:55,639 --> 00:42:56,280
The clothes are washed.

458
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:56,880
Brush the shoes.

459
00:42:56,881 --> 00:42:58,001
Call me when dinner's ready.

460
00:43:45,494 --> 00:43:49,860
We're all actors. If we just
want to survive, there's no future.

461
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:52,686
But I really like you...

462
00:43:52,783 --> 00:43:54,430
Do you not understand what I'm saying?

463
00:43:55,979 --> 00:43:58,966
You're always caught up
in some bizarre emotions.

464
00:44:19,920 --> 00:44:22,320
This one's mine, right? I'm a bigger size.

465
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:31,440
This shirt looks like mine, too.

466
00:44:36,320 --> 00:44:39,440
Is your grandpa's wife big too?

467
00:44:45,519 --> 00:44:46,719
Grandpa's wife?

468
00:44:47,639 --> 00:44:48,639
Who's that?

469
00:44:51,679 --> 00:44:52,920
Holy crap, Han Lu.

470
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:11,880
Whose wife is big?

471
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:15,800
Hmm?

472
00:45:28,440 --> 00:45:30,280
Ah, let's go.

473
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:33,416
For the past 20 years,
tea has been sold...

474
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:34,816
by emphasizing its
cultural significance.

475
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:36,680
And marketed to
high-net-worth individuals.

476
00:45:36,840 --> 00:45:38,575
The idea was to
promote it as a collectible.

477
00:45:38,599 --> 00:45:40,800
But that consumer
market is already saturated.

478
00:45:41,039 --> 00:45:43,480
And the market for the younger
generation is still untapped.

479
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:46,439
So now, selling tea has to align with...

480
00:45:46,440 --> 00:45:48,320
the lifestyle of today's youth.

481
00:45:49,039 --> 00:45:50,079
Live in the moment.

482
00:45:50,199 --> 00:45:51,320
Enjoy the present.

483
00:45:51,440 --> 00:45:53,038
If you have good tea, you
don't have to hide it away.

484
00:45:53,039 --> 00:45:54,199
Drink it whenever you want.

485
00:45:55,199 --> 00:45:56,479
Mr. Feng, your insights are very unique.

486
00:45:56,480 --> 00:45:58,015
Just what you'd expect from a big star.

487
00:45:58,039 --> 00:45:59,480
No, it's just my humble opinion.

488
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:02,679
I just have a better understanding
of consumer psychology.

489
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:05,280
My brother has a master's
degree in business from abroad.

490
00:46:07,079 --> 00:46:08,519
It's rare for you to praise me.

491
00:46:09,320 --> 00:46:11,198
This time, we have Qingtian to thank...

492
00:46:11,199 --> 00:46:12,799
for getting Mr. Feng
to do a livestream for us.

493
00:46:12,800 --> 00:46:15,440
The tea business hasn't been
doing well these past two years.

494
00:46:15,599 --> 00:46:17,679
We tea farmers can't sell our tea.

495
00:46:17,880 --> 00:46:20,199
In a business that
depends on the weather...

496
00:46:20,239 --> 00:46:21,679
the tea farmers are going hungry.

497
00:46:25,639 --> 00:46:28,079
Changyang, take my
brother to see the warehouse.

498
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:29,920
Teacher Fu can take me.

499
00:46:30,639 --> 00:46:32,439
I'm really not as
knowledgeable as Changyang.

500
00:46:32,599 --> 00:46:34,000
Which tea is where...

501
00:46:34,119 --> 00:46:35,239
Changyang knows best.

502
00:48:32,480 --> 00:48:34,799
The tea stored here is aged ripe pu'er.

503
00:48:34,800 --> 00:48:36,280
From the 90s to the 2000s.

504
00:48:36,639 --> 00:48:37,880
Over here is the raw pu'er.

505
00:48:38,320 --> 00:48:40,440
This row is tea stored from the 70s.

506
00:48:41,639 --> 00:48:43,239
I don't need to know all this.

507
00:48:44,679 --> 00:48:46,800
At first, we planned
to organize it by region.

508
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:48,479
But considering that tea
from different regions...

509
00:48:48,480 --> 00:48:50,280
can be hard for
drinkers to distinguish...

510
00:48:50,719 --> 00:48:52,599
except for types like Molie and Xigui.

511
00:48:53,519 --> 00:48:54,799
Molie tea has a strong 'cha qi'.

512
00:48:55,000 --> 00:48:56,440
It's bold, like a general.

513
00:48:56,800 --> 00:48:58,040
Xigui has a heavy floral aroma.

514
00:48:58,599 --> 00:49:00,199
It's known as the 'dancing tea'.

515
00:49:06,079 --> 00:49:07,679
I don't need a lecture from you.

516
00:49:10,519 --> 00:49:12,376
The total inventory in
the warehouse is 17 tons.

517
00:49:12,400 --> 00:49:13,518
We plan to use one ton to make...

518
00:49:13,519 --> 00:49:15,055
blended flavors that
young people will like.

519
00:49:15,079 --> 00:49:16,198
If the market response is good...

520
00:49:16,199 --> 00:49:17,480
I already know all this.

521
00:49:18,840 --> 00:49:20,800
If you really don't know what to say...

522
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:23,199
then don't say
anything. Just lead the way.
